It is Friday, and for me it means opening a Spotify and going to &quot;New releases for you&quot;. This week I was very disappointed. Three of those releases are some ambient background music with identical musical themes:
&quot;The Pink Rabbit, The Old Boy - World&quot;  
&quot;Unravel Project, Catch My Soul - Heart&quot;  
&quot;Davide Sari, Ambre Some - May&quot;  
(sorry, no links, I do not want to support acts like that)<p>Always two artists, single word song name, very similar album art, and naturally those songs are like copies of each other.<p>So will Spotify take measures against these ghost artists or should I just cancel my subscription?
